Description: Body sherd of Chian, possibly Simple Animal Style, pottery phiale mesomphalos; white slip; interior glazed streaky black with three added white bands above part of elaborate rosette in white outline with added red centres; exterior: reserved above, glazed below; inscription on exterior.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GD.1941) (phase 2)
